### Assertion 2: Click 'AAPL' ticker badge — company profile modal opens
**FAIL** — Clicking the AAPL ticker badge does NOTHING. No modal opens.

Root cause: The company profile modal HTML markup (`#company-profile-overlay` and its children) was NEVER added to `frontend/terminal.html`.

Evidence:
  - `grep -r "company-profile" frontend/terminal.html` → No matches found
  - `grep -r "company-profile" static/terminal.html` → No matches found
  - `grep -r "company-profile" --include="*.html"` across entire project → No matches found
  - In-browser check: `document.getElementById('company-profile-overlay')` → null
  - In-browser check: `document.getElementById('company-profile-close')` → null
  - In-browser check: `document.getElementById('company-profile-title')` → null
  - In-browser check: `document.getElementById('company-profile-body')` → null

The JS code at terminal-app.js:1455-1456 does:
  ```js
  const overlay = $("#company-profile-overlay");
  if (!overlay) return;  // ← silently returns here because element doesn't exist
  ```

The existing detail-modal-overlay (at frontend/terminal.html line 395-410) shows the required pattern:
  ```html
  <div class="modal-overlay" id="detail-modal-overlay">
    <div class="modal detail-modal">
      <div class="modal-header">...</div>
      <div class="modal-body detail-modal-body"><!-- Populated by JS --></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  ```

A matching HTML block is needed for the company profile modal, but was never created.

