## Acceptance Criteria Verification

### AC1: Clicking a ticker badge opens a company profile modal
FAIL — Badge click handler exists (terminal-app.js:1185-1189), calls openCompanyProfile().
  openCompanyProfile() early-returns at line 1456 because #company-profile-overlay is null.
  The overlay HTML element was never added to the template.

### AC2: 'Fundamentals' tab displays: company name, sector, market cap, description, logo, homepage link
FAIL — Cannot verify (modal doesn't open). JS rendering code exists at renderCompanyFundamentals()
  (terminal-app.js:1502-1541) but is never reached.

### AC3: Data fetched from /api/market/:symbol/details
FAIL — The fetch at terminal-app.js:1480 is never reached due to the early return at line 1456.
  The endpoint exists and responds (returns 401 without auth).

### AC4: Loading state shown while fetching
FAIL — Loading skeleton HTML is built at lines 1465-1473 but never shown (overlay is null).

### AC5: Modal matches dark terminal theme
PARTIAL — CSS styles exist at terminal.css lines 1868-2063 (.company-profile-modal, .cp-* classes).
  Cannot verify visual rendering since the modal doesn't open.

### AC6: Typecheck passes
PASS — Vite build exits 0.

### AC7: Verify in browser — click ticker then modal opens with fundamentals data
FAIL — See Assertion 2.

## What exists vs what's missing

PRESENT:
  - JS click handler: terminal-app.js:1185-1189 (badge click → openCompanyProfile)
  - JS modal logic: terminal-app.js:1449-1550 (openCompanyProfile, renderCompanyFundamentals, closeCompanyProfile)
  - JS close handlers: terminal-app.js:1212-1221 (X button, overlay click)
  - JS escape handler: terminal-app.js:1287 (Escape key priority)
  - CSS styles: terminal.css:1868-2063 (full modal styling)
  - State fields: terminal-app.js:81-84 (companyProfileOpen, companyProfileSymbol, etc.)

MISSING:
  - HTML template markup in frontend/terminal.html — no `#company-profile-overlay` element
  - The modal overlay, modal container, header, title, close button, tab bar, body — ALL absent from HTML

